<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>Relocation Evaluator</title>
{% include "_style.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>
<h1>Relocation Evaluator</h1>

<p class="site-intro">
A personal research tool evaluating US cities across ~65 data points &mdash; schools, safety,
climate, water and power infrastructure, land and legal considerations, and self-sufficiency
&mdash; using live web search paired with an LLM. It's public because the research might be
useful to someone else looking at the same cities, but it's not open for anyone to run: every
evaluation makes real, billed AI API calls, so new cities are added by the site owner one at a
time, and only the owner can trigger a new evaluation.
</p>
<p class="site-intro">
The Family Fit and Self-Sufficiency scores below are deliberately subjective &mdash; they
reflect one specific family's priorities and weightings, not an objective ranking. That family
is small, isn't chasing an off-grid, middle-of-nowhere, maximally-isolated location, and isn't
optimizing for zero risk either &mdash; some tradeoffs are acceptable.
<a href="scoring.html">See exactly how the scores are calculated</a>.
</p>

{% if cities|length >= 2 %}
<p><a href="compare.html">&#8646; Compare two cities side by side</a></p>
{% endif %}

{% if cities %}
<ul class="city-list">
{% for city in cities %}
  <li class="city-row">
    <div class="city-info">
      <a href="{{ city.href }}">{{ city.city }}, {{ city.state }}</a><br>
      <span class="county">{{ city.county }} &middot; {{ city.completion.valid }}/{{ city.completion.total }} fields ({{ city.completion.percent }}%)</span>
    </div>
    {% if city.lens_scores %}
    <div class="fit-scores city-fit-scores">
    {% for lens_key, lens in city.lens_scores.items() %}
      {% if lens.state == "scored" %}
        {% set css_class = "fit-strong" if lens.fit_label == "Strong Fit" else ("fit-good" if lens.fit_label == "Good Fit" else "fit-weak") %}
        <span class="fit-badge has-tooltip {{ css_class }}" tabindex="0"><span class="fit-lens-name">{{ lens.label }}:</span> {{ lens.fit_label }}{% if lens.reason %}<span class="tooltip-text">{{ lens.reason }}</span>{% endif %}</span>
      {% elif lens.state == "dealbreaker" %}
        <span class="fit-badge has-tooltip fit-dealbreaker" tabindex="0"><span class="fit-lens-name">{{ lens.label }}:</span> Dealbreaker{% if lens.reason %}<span class="tooltip-text">{{ lens.reason }}</span>{% endif %}</span>
      {% elif lens.state == "needs_data" %}
        <span class="fit-badge has-tooltip fit-needs-data" tabindex="0"><span class="fit-lens-name">{{ lens.label }}:</span> Needs data{% if lens.reason %}<span class="tooltip-text">{{ lens.reason }}</span>{% endif %}</span>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% endif %}
  </li>
{% endfor %}
</ul>
{% else %}
<p class="empty">No cities evaluated yet.</p>
{% endif %}

{% if cities %}
<p><a href="scoring.html">&#9432; How the Fit scores are calculated</a></p>
{% endif %}
</body>
</html>
